Class WheelStrut

  • java.lang.Object
    • WheelStrut
  • public class WheelStrut
extends Object
    This class models the Wheel Structure of the Airplane with a given number of wheels. also, checks if it's safe to use

      static String ERROR_NEGATIVE_WHEELS

    • Method Detail

      • reviewPressure

        public double reviewPressure​(double basePressure)
        Verifies that the pressure of each wheel of the strut is within the range [basePressure-Wheel.THRESHOLD; basePressure+Wheel.THRESHOLD]. If so, the wheel pressure is correct, and remains unmodified. If don't, the pressure in the wheel will be updated to the basePressure. If the basePressure is negative, the pressure won't update it and a error message will appear
        Parameters:
        basePressure - It's the pressure taken to check if the pressure of the wheel is in that range
        Returns:
        The sum of the pressures of the wheels in the WheelStrut
